The paper discusses a planning algorithm that draws from both early and recent developments in the field of domain independent planning, and proposes novel flaw selection strategies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions support for planning with durative actions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of heuristic techniques and reachability analysis further suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the planner and its competitiveness with other established planners, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
